            <h3 id="time-management">1. Create a Daily Time Management Plan</h3>
            <p>Time management is key when balancing university studies and Quran memorization. Here’s how you can plan effectively:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Start with a clear schedule that includes study hours and Quran memorization time.</li>
                <li>Use a planner or a mobile app to stay organized.</li>
                <li>Prioritize challenging tasks during peak productivity hours.</li>
                <li>Break long sessions into shorter, focused study periods.</li>
                <li>Review and adjust your plan daily for maximum efficiency.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>A structured schedule reduces stress and ensures steady progress in both academics and Hifz.</p>

            <h3 id="prioritize-tasks">2. Prioritize Tasks with Academic Deadlines</h3>
            <p>Staying on top of academic deadlines ensures that both studies and memorization progress smoothly. Organize tasks by:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Listing academic and Quran-related tasks in order of urgency.</li>
                <li>Breaking large tasks into smaller, manageable steps.</li>
                <li>Pairing lighter academic tasks with Quran revision to balance workload.</li>
                <li>Regularly updating your task list to accommodate changes.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>This approach prevents last-minute stress and keeps your memorization on track.</p>

            <h3 id="fixed-hours">3. Allocate Fixed Hours for Quran Hifz</h3>
            <p>Consistency is crucial for effective memorization. Set aside a specific time each day when you can focus without distractions. Ideal times include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Early mornings after Fajr prayer.</li>
                <li>Quiet evening hours before bed.</li>
                <li>Breaks between university classes.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Inform those around you about your schedule to avoid interruptions. Start with small goals (e.g., one or two Ayahs) and gradually increase as you progress.</p>

            <!-- Journey Button -->
